sg.danielneutrinos.jmdictlib.data

Class JMEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • sg.danielneutrinos.jmdictlib.data.JMEntry

  • public class JMEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    Entries consist of kanji elements, reading elements, general information and sense elements. Each entry must have at least one reading element and one sense element. Others are optional.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      private int entrySequence
      A unique numeric sequence number for each entry
      private java.util.List<KanjiElement> kanjiElements
      The kanji element, or in its absence, the reading element, is the defining component of each entry.
      private java.util.List<ReadingElement> readingElements
      The reading element typically contains the valid readings of the word(s) in the kanji element using modern kanadzukai.
      private java.util.List<Sense> senses
      The sense element will record the translational equivalent of the Japanese word, plus other related information.

    • Field Detail

      • entrySequence

        private int entrySequence
        A unique numeric sequence number for each entry

      • kanjiElements

        private java.util.List<KanjiElement> kanjiElements
        The kanji element, or in its absence, the reading element, is the defining component of each entry.

      • readingElements

        private java.util.List<ReadingElement> readingElements
        The reading element typically contains the valid readings of the word(s) in the kanji element using modern kanadzukai. Where there are multiple reading elements, they will typically be alternative readings of the kanji element.

      • senses

        private java.util.List<Sense> senses
        The sense element will record the translational equivalent of the Japanese word, plus other related information. Where there are several distinctly different meanings of the word, multiple sense elements will be employed.
